LAGOS – Dele Ajiboye, the Plateau United goalkeeper, has denounced the rumours making the round since last week that the management of the Peace Boys had placed the players of the club on half salary, saying the club’s general manager, Pius Henwan, was misquoted by the media. Recall that after the former CAF Champions League campaigners were pegged 2-0 at home by Kwara United in one of the match-day one games of the 2020/2021 Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) season, the club, through Henwan, reportedly placed the players on half salary, a development that attracted widespread condemnation. However, in a chat with our correspondent, the Super Eagles goalie said the general manager was quoted out of contest, denying the half salary saga. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “Don’t mind the media that reported it; it was not the way our general manager said it. “The man said if we do not improve from now till January, we will be placed on half salary. He was misquoted by the media. Nigerians Must Look Forward To Prosperous 2021 – Makinde Anambra: One Dead, Four Injured In Multiple Motor Accidents “The way he addressed the players on that day was not the way they put it on paper. “He meant to say that if we did not buckle up within the time frame, they will cut our salaries. “Let me tell you, he just want us to be serious and take our games serious; it is not as if the management means it. The Peace Boys, it will be recalled, lost out in the CAF Champions League after they were eliminated by Tanzanian giants, Simba SC, over two legs. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION